  "text": "Fas-mediated apoptosis is triggered by caspase 8-mediated cleavage of the pro-apoptotic protein Bid and is inhibited by Bcl-2. [CITATION_1] Although both normal and malignant T-cell lines expressed Fas on the cell surface (supplemental Figure 9 ), levels of Bcl-2 were significantly higher in CD5 CAR T cells ( Figure 4D -E). Conversely, malignant T cells expressed more Bid ( Figure 4F ), which correlates with the enhanced sensitivity of T-ALL and T-lymphoma cell lines to Fas-mediated cell death.",
